Some notes about β distribition

β(a, b) = Γ(a) Γ(b) / Γ(a + b), where Γ(n+1) = n Γ(n)

β(a, b) is also defined as

\begin{equation} \int_{0}^{1} x^{a-1} (1-x)^{b-1} dx \end{equation}

using Distributions, StatsPlots
l = @layout [a b; c d]
p1 = plot(Beta(0.5,0.5), legend=false, title="0.5, 0.5")
p2 = plot(Beta(2,1), legend=false, title="2, 1")
p3 = plot(Beta(4,4), legend=false, title="4, 4")
p4 = plot(Beta(2,10), legend=false, title="2, 10")
plot(p1, p2, p3, p4, layout = l)

Beta is a flexible distribution on (0,1) and thus is commmonly used to represent unknown probabilities. Let r.v. $X$ be the number of heads in n tosses of a coin with heas probability $p$, which is unknown. We can model $p$ ~ Beta($a$, $b$). So given $p$, the conditional distribution for $X$ is, $ X|p \sim \text{Bin}(n, p)$. If $f(p)$ denotes the prior distribution of $p$, and $f(p | X=k)$ denotes the posterior distribution given $k$ heads out of $n$, \begin{equation} f(p) = \frac{1}{\beta(a, b)} p^{a-1} (1-p)^{b-1} \end{equation}

\begin{equation} f(p | X=k) = \frac{P(X = k | p) f(p)} {P(X=k)} \end{equation}

\begin{equation} f(p | X=k) = \frac{{n \choose k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k} \cdot \frac{1}{\beta(a,b)} p^{a-1} (1-p)^{b-1}}{P(X=k)} \end{equation}

Since $f(p | X=k)$ is the function of $p$, we can drop all other terms at the expense of the equality turning into proportionality.

\begin{equation} f(p | X=k) \propto p^{k+a-1} (1-p)^{n-k+b-1} \end{equation}

Which is $\beta(a+k, b+n-k)$. Thus if the prior is $\beta(a, b)$ then posterior $p | X=k = \beta(a+k, b+n-k)$. We are just adding the number of observed heads to $a$ and tails to $b$.

using Interact, Plots
Ns = 1:100
p_true = 0.8
data = rand(Bernoulli(p_true), last(Ns))
prior_belief = Beta(1, 1)

animation = @animate for (i, N) in enumerate(Ns)
    heads = sum(data[1:i-1])
    tails = N - heads
    updated_belief = Beta(prior_belief.α + heads, prior_belief.β + tails)

    plot(updated_belief,
        title = "Updated belief after $N observations",
        xlabel = "probability of heads",
        legend = nothing, xlim = (0,1), yticks=[], fill=0, α=0.2, w=3)
    vline!([p_true])
end
gif(animation, fps=3)
